OpenAI, Oracle plan 1 gigawatt Stargate data center in Michigan with Related Digital
data.description:
(Reuters) -OpenAI, Oracle and Related Digital said on Thursday they would build a data-center campus of more than 1 gigawatt in Saline Township, Michigan, as part of their Stargate push to expand U.S. artificial intelligence infrastructure capacity.

The project would start construction in early 2026 and is part of Oracle and OpenAI's previously announced 4.5-GW expansion under the Stargate program. It brings Stargate to more than 8 GW of planned capacity and more than $450 billion in investment over the next three years.

The companies said it was a multi-billion dollar investment, without disclosing the exact figure. Industry executives have said 1 GW of computing power, enough to power roughly 750,000 U.S. homes, can cost around $50 billion.

Related Digital will develop the project, which is expected to create more than 2,500 union construction jobs.

"This project will help ensure Michigan is a key part of building the AI infrastructure that will power the next generation of American innovation," said Peter Hoeschele, OpenAI's vice president of industrial compute.

(Reporting by Aditya Soni and Akash Sriram in Bengaluru; Editing by Shilpi Majumdar)

Coinbase Global 3Q Sales Climb as Trading Volumes Rise
data.description:
By Katherine Hamilton


Coinbase Global recorded a jump in sales as trading volumes increased in the third quarter.

The cryptocurrency marketplace on Thursday posted a profit of $437.1 million, or $1.50 a share, in the quarter ended Sept. 30, compared with $75.5 million, or 28 cents a share, a year earlier.

Stripping out certain one-time items, adjusted per-share earnings were $1.44, ahead of the $1.32 anticipated by analysts, according to FactSet.

Revenue jumped 55% to $1.87 billion. Analysts surveyed by FactSet forecast revenue of $1.80 billion. Global crypto market spot trading volumes increased 38% quarter over quarter and rose 29% in the U.S.

The company increased tradable spot assets as part of its initiative to be the "everything exchange," and now covers about 90% of the total crypto asset market capitalization.

In the current fourth quarter, Coinbase expects subscription and services revenue to be $710 million to $790 million, which would beat the $766.6 million Wall Street is projecting.

Gilead Sciences Lifts Outlook with Higher 3Q Sales, Profit
data.description:
By Dean Seal


Gilead Sciences raised its full-year profit guidance and said royalty and contract revenue buoyed third-quarter sales while demand for its Covid-19 treatment sank.

The biopharmaceutical company said Thursday that it now expects earnings of $6.65 to $6.85 a share for the full year, up from its previous outlook of $5.85 to $6.15 a share.

Adjusted earnings, which strip out one-time items, are now on track to hit $8.05 to $8.25 a share, Gilead said, adding a dime to the low-end of its previous range.

The company also bumped up its product sales outlook, adding $100 million to the low end of guidance it previously gave.

Third-quarter revenue rose 3% to $7.8 billion, topping analyst forecasts for $7.45 billion, according to FactSet.

Product sales were down 2% at $7.3 billion due to declines for Veklury, the Covid-19 treatment that saw a 60% drop in sales, and its cell therapy portfolio. That was partially offset by growth for its HIV products and Livdelzi, a liver-disease treatment. Excluding Veklury, product sales were up 4%.

Royalty, contract and other revenue streams meanwhile increased to $424 million from just $30 million a year earlier.

Gilead reported quarterly profit of $3.05 billion, or $2.43 a share, compared with $1.25 billion, or $1 a share, last year. The year-earlier quarter included a pre-tax, in-process research and development impairment charge that didn't recur.

Adjusted earnings were $2.47 a share. Analysts polled by FactSet had been expecting $2.13 a share.
